=== Others ===
* {{ill|lt=Koshin Tower|Q11486001|qid=Q11486001|1=Kōshin-tō}}
** Built in {{ill|lt=1980|Q2439|qid=Q2439|1=1980}} (1980) using one of the cornerstones of the former second torii gate of Kasami Shrine.
* {{ill|lt=Loyalty Monument|Q11274518|qid=Q11274518|1=monument to the loyal dead}} ({{ill|lt=Sino-Japanese War|Q178687|qid=Q178687|lt=Conquering and Qing Monument|1=First Sino-Japanese War}}, {{ill|lt=Russo-Japanese War|Q159950|qid=Q159950|lt=Russo-Japanese War|1=Russo-Japanese War}} Loyalty Monument, Martyred Soldiers Monument)
** It was originally installed in a different location, but was moved to the shrine grounds.

=== Main rituals ===
Based on "Shikiuchi Kinpeisha Kasami Shrine Bookmark".
* January 1st - {{ill|lt=Saidan Festival|Q11546824|qid=Q11546824|1=Saitan-sai}}, Good Luck Prayer Festival, Traffic Safety Festival
* February Setsubun - {{ill|lt=Setsubun|Q746798|qid=Q746798|1=Setsubun}} Festival
* February 14th of the lunar calendar - Akiba Festival
* February 20th - {{ill|lt=prayer festival|Q118906710|qid=Q118906710|1=Kinensai}}・Okuwa Festival
* March 15th - Sumiyoshi Festival
* First Saturday of April - Okunomiya Festival/Suijin Festival
* Last Sunday of July - {{ill|lt=Great Purification|Q11261910|qid=Q11261910|1=Ōharae-shiki}} Shinto ritual
* Second Sunday before October 15th - {{ill|lt=Reitaisai|Q11385469|qid=Q11385469|lt=Reitaisai|1=Reisai}}
** It used to be held on October 14th and 15th every year. A flower mikoshi is carried out. Previously, the Kenka Mikoshi was dedicated, but it was temporarily suspended due to an accident, but the "Rokken Mikoshi Association" centered around {{ill|lt=Sohara Rokkencho|Q131900816|qid=Q131900816|1=Sohara Rokkencho}} has revived the Kenka Mikoshi as a mock performance.<ref>{{Cite web |Japanese book |url=https://rokken-mikoshi.jimdosite.com/ |title=Rokuken Mikoshi Association |accessdate=2025-05-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |Japanese book |url=https://www.chunichi.co.jp/article/791540 |title=Vertically ``Fighting Mikoshi'' Regular festival at Kakamigahara Kasami Shrine |newspaper={{ill|lt=Chunichi Shimbun|Q904678|qid=Q904678|1=Chunichi Shimbun}} |date=2023-10-19}}</ref>.* November 15th - {{ill|lt=Shichigosan|Q1072387|qid=Q1072387|1=Shichi-Go-San}} Festival
* November 23rd - New Grain Thanksgiving
* December 31st - {{ill|lt=New Year's Eve|Q7245702|qid=Q7245702|1=Chinese New Year's Eve}} Festival
* 1st and 15th of every month - Monthly Festival

=== Cultural assets ===
* Wooden guardian dog
** A wooden {{ill|lt=guardian dog|Q20155846|qid=Q20155846|1=Komainu}} approximately 115cm tall. It is thought to have been produced in the early {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|qid=Q184963|1=Edo period}} period. City-designated cultural property ({{ill|lt=1974|Q2478|qid=Q2478|1=1974}} (June 26, 1974)) <ref name="City-designated cultural property">{{Cite web|Japanese book|url=https://www.city.kakamigahara.lg.jp/kankobunka/bunkazai/1005178.html |title=City-designated cultural property |access-date=2025-03-04 |publisher=Kakamigahara City}}</ref><ref name="Kasami Shrine"/><ref name="Wooden guardian dog">{{Cite web|Japanese book|url=https://www.city.kakamigahara.lg.jp/kankobunka/bunkazai/1011515/1005217.html |title=Is there actually only one “guardian dog”? Elegant wooden sculpture |access-date=2025-03-04 |publisher=Kakamigahara City}}</ref>.
* Kasami Shrine Lion Head** A wooden lion head donated by Noguchi Village, Kagami District in {{ill|lt=Enpo|Q1145735|qid=Q1145735|1=Enpō}}3 ({{ill|lt=1675|Q7624|qid=Q7624|1=1675}}). During the annual shrine festival procession in October, a lion head leads the mikoshi procession. City-designated cultural property ({{ill|lt=1970|Q2474|qid=Q2474|1=1970}} (March 23, 1974)) <ref name="City-designated cultural property"/><ref name="Kasami Shrine"/><ref name="Lion Head">{{Cite web|Japanese book|url=https://www.city.kakamigahara.lg.jp/kankobunka/bunkazai/1011515/1005225.html |title=A regional treasure where the legend of "Oshishi-sama" is passed down |access-date=2025-03-04 |publisher=Kakamigahara City}}</ref>.

=== Location ===
